  const [comment, setComment] = useState("");

  // ðŸ”´ BAD! Avoid: Resetting state on prop change in an Effect
  useEffect(() => {
    setComment("");
  }, [userId]);
  // ...
}
```

This is inefficient - `ProfilePage` first renders with stale data, then re-renders. Itâ€™s also messy, since you'd need to reset state in every nested component.

A better approach: treat each userâ€™s profile as a separate one by giving it a unique `key`. Split the component and pass a `key` from the outer to the inner part.

